    <briefdescription>
<para>const and non-const tensors in the appropriate address space </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>__TTL_typedef_tensor_t</para>
</simplesect>
Use of macros to ensure that structs are EXACTLY the same, along for the compiler to remove duplication and potentially a <ref refid="TTL__int__tensors_8h_1af55285c5c289c327379be3725265949a" kindref="member">TTL_int_tensor_t</ref> to be safely case to a <ref refid="TTL__int__tensors_8h_1a6f8d3bc7ab2c427d51a3addc5417bce0" kindref="member">TTL_const_int_tensor_t</ref>.</para>
<para>Do not add a cast for <ref refid="TTL__int__tensors_8h_1a6f8d3bc7ab2c427d51a3addc5417bce0" kindref="member">TTL_const_int_tensor_t</ref> to <ref refid="TTL__int__tensors_8h_1af55285c5c289c327379be3725265949a" kindref="member">TTL_int_tensor_t</ref> because that is not safe. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
